    "body": "### Problem\n\n<img width=\"957\" height=\"381\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/5b3a9ca3-75a7-4854-89c5-39782ae71312\" />\n\nThe error still occurs. Additionally (maybe it's a separate issue) I can observe empty space below one-line messages. \n\n<img width=\"68\" height=\"186\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6f99068b-b740-4c52-a056-0d2cd17df3fe\" />\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\ninit.lua:\n\n```lua\nrequire('vim._core.ui2').enable({enable = true, msg = {target = 'msg'}})\nvim.go.cmdheight = 0\n\nlocal interval = 150\nlocal msgIndex = 0\n\nlocal function printAndFclose()\n  local msg = {{tostring(msgIndex) .. '\\n'}}\n  vim.api.nvim_echo(msg, true, {})\n  vim.cmd.fclose({bang = true})\nend\n\nlocal function schedule(len)\n  local timer = assert(vim.uv.new_timer())\n\n  timer:start(0, interval, function ()\n    if msgIndex >= len then timer:stop(); timer:close(); return end\n    vim.schedule(printAndFclose)\n    msgIndex = msgIndex + 1\n  end)\nend\n\nlocal lines = 14\nvim.go.lines = lines\nlocal msgCnt = math.ceil(lines / 2) + 1\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('UIEnter', {\n  once = true,\n  callback = function ()\n    schedule(msgCnt)\n    vim.wait(interval * msgCnt + 1000, function ()\n      vim.cmd.fclose({bang = true})\n    end)\n  end,\n})\n```\n\n- `nvim --clean -u init.lua`\n- wait for the messages to disappear\n- submit `:lua print('x\\nx\\nx')`\n- look into `:messages` (not sure if 100% reproducible).\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo errors\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-2410+g844caca881\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDebian Sid\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nfrom repo",
